	<h1>FIR - Fairways in regulation</h1>
	<p>For fairways in regulation (FIR) we need to know whether you hit the fairway or not, and where the ball came to a stop. You can only add FIR data to holes that are par 4 or greater.</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<h2>Entering your data</h2>
	<div class="floatEnder"></div>	
	<div style="float: left; width: 101px; margin-right: 10px;">
		<p><img class="imgBorder" src="/tracker/wl/lovegolf/images/im-help-fir-missed.gif" height="47" width="99" alt="FIR missed" /></p>
	</div>
	<div style="float: right; width: 410px;">
		<p>If you <strong>failed</strong> to hit the fairway, leave the checkbox <strong>unticked</strong>. Then choose where the ball came to a stop. Your options are:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Left</strong> - Off the fairway to the left. This includes shots that went out of bounds.</li>
			<li><strong>Right</strong> - Off the fairway to the Right. This includes shots that went out of bounds.</li>
			<li><strong>Short</strong> - Short of the fairway.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="floatEnder"></div>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<div style="float: left; width: 101px; margin-right: 10px;">
		<p><img class="imgBorder" src="/tracker/wl/lovegolf/images/im-help-fir-hit.gif" height="47" width="99" alt="FIR hit" /></p>
	</div>
	<div style="float: right; width: 410px;">
		<p>If you <strong>succeeded</strong> in hitting the fairway, click the checkbox to tick it. Then choose where the ball came to a stop. Your options are:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Centre</strong> - On the fairway down the centre.</li>
			<li><strong>Left</strong> - On the fairway to the left.</li>
			<li><strong>Right</strong> - On the fairway to the right.</li>
			<li><strong>Short</strong> - On the fairway, but not full distance.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="floatEnder"></div>
	
</div>